<HEADLINE>
<P>
LA JOLLA HALF MARATHON WILL BE RUN SUNDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The La Jolla Half Marathon, billed as the fourth-largest race of its type in 
the nation, begins at 7:30 a.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The course starts at the Del Mar Fairgrounds, heads south along the coast and 
winds up at La Jolla Cove Scripps Park. Also included in the activities are 
2-mile and 5-mile jaunts. 
</P>
<P>
The race, which offers a $500 prize to the male or female that breaks the 
course record, is limited to 4,000 entrants. Deadline for registration is 
Saturday, and no sign-ups will be accepted the day of the race. 
</P>
<P>
All profits will go to the La Jolla Kiwanis Foundation to help youth projects 
there. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call 272-8316. 
</P>
</TEXT>
