<HEADLINE>
<P>
S&amp;L CRISIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The solution to the savings and loan junk bond crisis is not that difficult. 
</P>
<P>
Just make possible a marketplace reversal. 
</P>
<P>
The government should set a five- to seven-year window during which period 
dividends would be deductible to corporations. Corporations would then be in a 
position to exchange debt for equity and permit stockholders a return on their 
investment without requiring them to sell their stake in the company. 
</P>
<P>
If capital gains taxes were reinstated, the process of economic health would be 
accelerated. Corporate performance would once again be evaluated on 
profitability and not on takeover speculation. 
</P>
<P>
ROBERT A. FINKELSTEIN 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
