<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego police said they arrested a speeding motorist who was carrying 300 
pounds of packaged marijuana in a pickup truck. 
</P>
<P>
Ramon Garcia, 40, was being held in the County Jail in lieu of $3,000 bail on 
suspicion of marijuana possession and speeding, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Police spokesman Bill Robinson said U. S. Customs Service agents asked for 
police help shortly before 10:30 p.m. Wednesday because Garcia was speeding on 
Interstate 5 north of California 52. 
</P>
<P>
A police officer stopped Garcia on I-805 and found the marijuana in the bed of 
the truck, Robinson said. 
</P>
