<P>
CARSON SWIMMER EARNS HIGH FINISHES AT CHAMPIONSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Claudine Martinez, 17, of Carson placed in three events at the recent National 
YMCA Short Course Swimming Championships held at Orlando, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
Martinez, who swims for the San Pedro and Peninsula YMCA, finished third in the 
200-yard individual medley, fourth in the 400-yard IM and 8th in the 1,650-yard 
freestyle. About 5,000 swimmers from more than 230 YMCAs participated in the 
four-day event. Others from the San Pedro and Peninsula YMCA who competed were 
Chris McAllister, Tina Leuthard, Rod Wallace, Heather Miller, Sarah McFarland 
and Deborah Kory (Rancho Palos Verdes), Roy Elliott and Sean Lemm (Redondo 
Beach), Alisa Scudamore (Palos Verdes Estates), Bruce Jones (San Pedro) and 
John Shieh (Torrance). 
</P>
