<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Money Supply Mixed: The Federal Reserve Board reported that nation's money 
supply known as M1 fell to a seasonally adjusted $805.6 billion from $808 
billion. 
</P>
<P>
A broader measure, known as M2, rose to a seasonally adjusted $3,275.8 billion 
from $3,269.3 billion the previous week. M1 includes cash in circulation, 
deposits in checking accounts and non-bank travelers checks. M2 is M1 plus 
accounts such as savings deposits and money market mutual funds. 
</P>
