<HEADLINE>
<P>
A GUILTY VERDICT IS ASSURED WHEN AN AUTO STANDS TRIAL FOR POLLUTING THE 
ENVIRONMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OAKLAND 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As part of an "alternative transportation day" at the Oakland offices of the 
Bay Area Rapid Transit system, an automobile was put on trial for contributing 
to the world's environmental ills. 
</P>
<P>
More than 200 cheering onlookers, including BART employees, attended the mock 
trial. After the car was found "guilty" of polluting and clogging up the 
freeways, bystanders took turns carrying out the sentence by smashing the 
vehicle with sledgehammers. 
</P>
<P>
"We urge you to strike a symbolic blow for cleaner air," said "Judge" Gregory 
Proops, who like many of the other trial participants, is a professional 
comedian. "But don't try this at home." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
OAKLAND (CA) -- TRANSPORTATION; AUTOMOBILES; TRIALS; BAY AREA RAPID TRANSIT 
DISTRICT; AIR POLLUTION 
</P>
