<P>
SOUNDING 
</P>
<P>
From Operation New Broom, an organization that wants to limit state politicians 
to two terms in office: 
</P>
<P>
 "Some people ask us, what about losing the 'benefit' of all that experience in 
office? . . . We answer this way: by November, our 40 state senators will have 
been in office an average of 17 years. In terms of 'experience,' then . . . has 
the drug problem gotten better . . . is the public health delivery system 
better . . . is the education of our children getting better . . . are 
state/local taxes higher or lower?" 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
EXIT LINE 
</P>
<P>
"You don't need to worry about me being on the take in Sacramento. I made mine 
before I got there." 
</P>
<P>
 -- State Sen. John Seymour, an Anaheim Republican who is running for 
lieutenant governor. 
</P>
