<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MEDFLIES FOUND IN 2 AREAS NOT BEING SPRAYED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Agricultural officials announced Thursday the discovery of two more 
Mediterranean fruit flies, this time in Azusa and Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
A single immature female Medfly was found near Azusa Tuesday in a previously 
uninfested area off Chadley Street, said Larry Cooper, an eradication project 
spokesman. The Pomona Medfly was found Wednesday in a loquat tree off Dudley 
Street, also in an uninfested area. No decision has been made on whether the 
areas will be treated with aerial malathion spraying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
