<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ACCUSED HIT-RUN DRIVER'S BLOOD ALCOHOL TESTS 
.46% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Glendale woman arrested after a hit-run accident had a blood-alcohol level 
more than five times the legal definition of drunk, authorities said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Cathylynne Marie Johnson, who weighs 105 pounds and had the equivalent of three 
quarters of a pint of bourbon in her system two hours after the accident, told 
investigating officers she did not drink, police said. She had a blood alcohol 
reading of .46%, said Deputy Dist. Atty. Michael Pargament. In California, a 
reading of .08% is considered proof of drunkenness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
