<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: $400-MILLION PROJECT NEAR MARINA APPROVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Channel Gateway, a $400-million high-rise office, condominium and apartment 
project next to Marina del Rey, won unanimous approval Thursday from the Los 
Angeles City Planning Commission after neighborhood leaders praised the massive 
development. 
</P>
<P>
The 16-acre project, planned by developer Jerome Snyder and associates, will 
include 512 condominiums in two 16-story towers, 544 apartments in clusters of 
four-story buildings, a 314,000-square-foot office building, and parking for 
more than 3,460 cars. 
</P>
<P>
Although the project will dramatically increase density in the already 
congested Lincoln Boulevard corridor, Venice community leaders said the largely 
residential development is a vast improvement over a shopping center and office 
complex once planned for the property. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
MARINA DEL REY (CA) -- DEVELOPMENT AND REDEVELOPMENT; LOS ANGELES -- 
DEVELOPMENT AND REDEVELOPMENT 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
