<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Viatcheslav Fetisov made a successful return to the Soviet national team, 
scoring a goal and adding three assists in a 10-1 blitz of Team USA at the 
World Hockey Championships in Bern, Switzerland. 
</P>
<P>
Fetisov, perhaps the greatest defenseman in international hockey during the 
1980s, feuded with Soviet Coach Victor Tikhonov and was cut briefly from the 
team before the 1989 tournament. 
</P>
<P>
He played in the NHL with New Jersey this season, and rejoined the Soviet team 
after the Devils' elimination from the Stanley Cup playoffs. The Soviet Union 
is 3-0, the United States 0-3. 
</P>
<P>
Detroit's Steve Yzerman scored three goals and set up the winner by Shawn Burr 
late in the third period as Team Canada (3-0) came back from a four-goal 
deficit to edge Finland, 6-5. Sweden (3-0) routed winless West Germany, 6-0, 
and Czechoslovakia also went 3-0 by beating Norway, 9-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
