<TEXT>
<P>
UPS AND DOWNS: A week ago Irvine Mayor Larry Agran was all smiles over being 
named to Rolling Stone's environmentalist Hall of Fame, but this week it's bad 
press. . . . The American Spectator, a national conservative journal, called 
Agran in a six-page article the "Evil Emperor of Irvine, California." . . . 
Agran is "a serpent (that) slipped into the garden," the article charges, but 
Agran calls it "desperation journalism." Steve Emmons and David Reyes 
</P>
