<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
MAN KILLED IN ROBBERY ATTEMPT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man was fatally shot this morning when he attempted to rob a camper in 
Angeles National Forest north of Castaic, the Los Angeles County Sheriff's 
Department said. 
</P>
<P>
The names of those involved in the 2:20 a.m. shooting at a campground called 
Frenchman's Flat were not released this morning as investigators attempted to 
sort out what happened, Deputy Rafael Estrada said. 
</P>
<P>
The campground is west of the Golden State Freeway between Castaic and Pyramid 
Reservoir. 
</P>
<P>
Estrada said three men apparently accosted a camper and were trying to rob him 
when the camper opened fire. One of the alleged robbers was struck and the 
other two fled. 
</P>
<P>
The injured man was taken to Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital, where he 
died. Estrada said the other two men were taken into custody near the 
campground and were being questioned this morning. The camper who fired the gun 
was not arrested. 
</P>
</TEXT>
