<P>
ISRAEL BIGGEST THREAT, IRAN TOLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TEHRAN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hundreds of thousands of Iranians converged on Tehran University today 
shouting, "Death to Israel, death to America!" President Ayatollah Hashemi 
Rafsanjani told them that fighting Israel is a Muslim's highest duty. 
</P>
<P>
The rally, combined with Friday prayers, marked "Qods (Jerusalem) Day," the 
last Friday of the Muslim fasting month of Ramadan, which Iran's late supreme 
leader, the Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini, dedicated to the support of the 
Palestinian cause. 
</P>
<P>
The crowd included women clad in black chadors, or Islamic head-to-toe 
coverings, and children. The annual turnout is widely seen as a barometer of 
the public support Iran's clerical leaders can muster. 
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani criticized Arab countries like Egypt which he said understand the 
danger from Israel but did nothing about it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
