<P>
RUZIMATOV JOINS AMERICAN BALLET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Faruk Ruzimatov, 26, once a dashing star of the Kirov Ballet, has joined the 
American Ballet Theater. 
</P>
<P>
He will dance with the company in its eight-week season at the Metropolitan 
Opera beginning May 7, the company said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Ruzimatov was praised when he danced here with the Kirov in 1987. He joined the 
Kirov in 1981, after his graduation from Leningrad's Vaganova Ballet Academy. 
</P>
