<P>
JAMES DOUGLAS FILES FOR DIVORCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COLUMBUS, Ohio 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Heavyweight champion James Douglas has filed for divorce, his wife's attorney 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
Robin Stith, attorney for Bertha Douglas, said Douglas alleges gross neglect of 
duty and incompatibility. Neither Douglas nor his manager, John Johnson, could 
be reached for comment. Johnson's son and executive assistant, John Johnson II, 
said the Douglas camp will not comment. 
</P>
<P>
Stith said Douglas filed for divorce Wednesday in Franklin County Domestic 
Relations Court. She said Bertha Douglas will contest it. "Mrs. Douglas and I 
have not yet figured out what our strategy will be. But we're going to protect 
her interests. That's for sure," Stith said. "My client doesn't want a 
divorce." 
</P>
</TEXT>
