<HEADLINE>
<P>
PANAMA INVASION'S LEADER NOMINATED FOR COMMAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush has nominated Lt. Gen. Carl Stiner, 53, who commanded the U.S. 
invasion of Panama, to be commander in chief of the U.S. Special Operations 
Command, the Pentagon announced Thursday. The command includes the Army 
Rangers, Green Berets, Navy SEALs and the Air Force Special Operations Wing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
